  "prompt": "What is a vitamin?",
  "response": "A vitamin is an organic compound and essential nutrient that an organism requires in limited amounts for normal physiological function. Vitamins are crucial for various bodily processes, including growth, metabolism, immune function, and overall health. They are typically obtained from the diet because the body either cannot synthesize them at all or cannot produce them in sufficient quantities.\n\nVitamins are classified into two categories based on their solubility:\n\n1. **Fat-soluble vitamins**: These vitamins dissolve in fats and oils and are stored in the body's fatty tissues and liver. They include:\n   - Vitamin A\n   - Vitamin D\n   - Vitamin E\n   - Vitamin K\n\n2. **Water-soluble vitamins**: These vitamins dissolve in water and are not stored in the body, meaning they need to be consumed regularly. They include:\n   - Vitamin C (ascorbic acid)\n   - B vitamins (e.g., thiamine (B1), riboflavin (B2), niacin (B3), pantothenic acid (B5), pyridoxine (B6), biotin (B7), folate (B9), and cobalamin (B12))\n\nDeficiencies or excesses of vitamins can lead to health problems, so maintaining a balanced diet is essential for meeting vitamin needs. In some cases, supplements may be recommended, but it's best to consult a healthcare professional before taking them.",
